{
  "local_port": 38956,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the best books for bank exam?",
  "response": "Preparing for bank exams requires a thorough understanding of various subjects such as **Quantitative Aptitude, Reasoning Ability, English Language, General Awareness, and Computer Knowledge**. Here are some of the best books recommended for bank exam preparation:\n\n---\n\n### **Quantitative Aptitude (Maths)**\n1. **Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations** by R.S. Aggarwal  \n   - Covers all basic to advanced topics with practice questions.\n2. **Fast Track Objective Arithmetic** by Arihant  \n   - Focuses on shortcuts and tricks for quick problem-solving.\n3. **Magical Book on Quicker Maths** by M. Tyra  \n   - Helps improve speed and accuracy in calculations.\n\n---\n\n### **Reasoning Ability**\n1. **A Modern Approach to Verbal & Non-Verbal Reasoning** by R.S. Aggarwal  \n   - Comprehensive guide for both verbal and non-verbal reasoning.\n2. **Analytical Reasoning** by M.K. Pandey  \n   - Focuses on analytical and logical reasoning problems.\n3. **Lucent's General Intelligence and Reasoning**  \n   - Good for basic concepts and practice.\n\n---\n\n### **English Language**\n1. **Objective General English** by S.P. Bakshi  \n   - Covers grammar, vocabulary, and comprehension.\n2. **Word Power Made Easy** by Norman Lewis  \n   - Helps improve vocabulary.\n3. **High School English Grammar and Composition** by Wren and Martin  \n   - Best for grammar fundamentals.\n\n---\n\n### **General Awareness**\n1. **Banking Awareness** by Arihant  \n   - Focuses on banking and financial awareness.\n2. **Manorama Yearbook**  \n   - Provides updates on current affairs and general knowledge.\n3. **Lucent's General Knowledge**  \n   - Comprehensive book for static GK.\n\n---\n\n### **Computer Knowledge**\n1. **Objective Computer Awareness** by Arihant  \n   - Covers basic to advanced computer concepts.\n2. **Computer Aptitude for Competitive Exams** by Kiran Prakashan  \n   - Focuses on computer-related questions.\n\n---\n\n### **Mock Tests and Practice Books**\n1. **Banking Awareness Practice Book** by Kiran Prakashan  \n   - Includes section-wise practice sets.\n2. **Reasoning Practice Book** by Kiran Prakashan  \n   - Contains previous years' questions and practice sets.\n3. **Quantitative Aptitude Practice Book** by Kiran Prakashan  \n   - Focuses on topic-wise practice.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Resources**\n- **Preliminary & Mains Exam Books** by Kiran Prakashan  \n- **Bank Exam Solved Papers** by Arihant  \n- **Online Study Materials** from platforms like Adda247, Testbook, and Oliveboard.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Bank Exam Preparation**\n1. Focus on **time management** and practice **mock tests** regularly.  \n2. Stay updated with **current affairs** and **banking awareness**.  \n3. Revise basic concepts and practice **previous years' question papers**.  \n4. Use **online resources** and apps for daily practice.\n\nChoose books based on your strengths and weaknesses, and ensure consistent practice for success!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
